body:
@rayjan0114 thanks! Unfortunately I did not see a big improvement, about 0.5 mAP increase on COCO after 50 epochs. 

I saw you controlled the colors of the cutouts, whereas mine are allowed to wander the full RGB space. I suppose the color should be selected randomly based on the prior distribution of the training dataset, something closer to a gaussian with mu and sigma ~128 ~50, but I doubt this will have much effect.

Another option is to add more smaller cutouts per image rather than one large one. What do you think?

@rayjan0114 yes as you say we remove the labels that are impossible to see. But unfortunately all the recent tests with cutouts show worse results, with the mAP decreasing with additional smaller cutouts. 

We've instead disabled the cutouts in the dataloader and moved to a 'mosaic dataloader' approach, which loads up a 4-image mosaic each time. This improved mAP about 1-2%, and we are now showing about exactly the same mAP as darknet. The mosaic dataloader operates by default now in the repo.

